he Book of Genesis, she was originally called <i>Sarai</i> (possibly meaning ‘contentious’ in Hebrew), but had her name changed by God to the more auspicious <i>Sarah</i> ‘princess’ in token of a greater blessing (Genesis 17:15, ‘And God said unto Abraham, As for Sarai thy wife, thou shalt not call her name Sarai, but Sarah shall her name be’). This has been one of the most enduringly popular girls' names."],"variants":[{"name":"Sara","meanings":["Variant of   Sarah .  This is the form used in the Greek of the New Testament (Hebrews 11:11)."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sarah Colemare was born in 1467, in Birmingham, Warwickshire, England, her father, William Colemare, was 37 and her mother, Sarah Collins, was 37. She had at least 2 sons with Richard De Hynton. She died in 1491, in Berkshire, England, at the age of 24."},"et":{"1467–1491":"1467–1491","1460–1520":"1460–1520","1488–1550":"1488–1550","1495–1548":"1495–1548","1430–1480":"1430–1480","1430–1490":"1430–1490","1467":"1467","1488":"1488","1520":"1520","1430":"1430","21 August 1488":"21. august 1488","1495":"1495","1550":"1550","1460":"1460","1480":"1480","1491":"1491","1490":"1490","1548":"1548","Birmingham, Birmingham, Warwickshire, England":"Birmingham, Warwickshire, England","Stanewick, Berkshire, England":"Berkshire, England","Birmingham, Warwickshire, England":"Birmingham, Warwickshire, England","Stavewyke, Berkshire, England":"Berkshire, England"},"fi":{"1467–1491":"1467–1491","1460–1520":"1460–1520","1488–1550":"1488–1550","1495–1548":"1495–1548","1430–1480":"1430–1480","1430–1490":"1430–1490","1467":"1467","1488":"1488","1520":"1520","1430":"1430","21 August 1488":"21. elokuuta 1488","1495":"1495","1550":"1550","1460":"1460","1480":"1480","1491":"1491","1490":"1490","1548":"1548","Birmingham, Birmingham, Warwickshire, England":"Birmingham, Warwickshire, England","Stanewick, Berkshire, England":"Berkshire, England","Birmingham, Warwickshire, England":"Birmingham, Warwickshire, England","Stavewyke, Berkshi